{"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/LAMP_(software_bundle)"}},"1":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raspberry_Pi"}},"2":{"type":"LINK","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"href":"https://github.com/christian-westbrook/orient"}}},"blocks":[{"key":"5579i","text":"Building a Blog Engine","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"30kjg","text":"","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dc5bb","text":"Hello, World!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f6crj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dj4a0","text":"Today I'd love to celebrate the reboot of christianwestbrook.dev by taking a look at its design with you. This site is a deployment of Anansi, an open-source blogging and portfolio engine. I designed Anansi to help me get up to speed and publishing blog posts as quickly as possible. Let's dive in!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3n3gi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6qp38","text":"Why a blog engine?","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"frt7o","text":"If you know anything about me, it's that I'm always learning. One of the best ways to transition new knowledge into long-term memory is to try teaching it to others. With that goal in mind, a blog seemed like the perfect medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6ncs5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9apsp","text":"Why open source?","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctmjp","text":"What a silly question!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"n7un","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2511v","text":"But why not just use WordPress?","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"elrlf","text":"I find that it's usually a better learning experience when you get your own hands dirty. You can learn a lot by reading, but it's all the more valuable to apply what you've learned to real problems.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"37pjv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4mm15","text":"Still, it's important to consider the expected outcome before re-inventing the wheel. I felt motivated to improve by designing, developing, and hosting a blog myself. You unlock a whole new can of fun when you're the one responsible for server security and performance!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3irjo","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"61v26","text":"There is also another more important reason for hosting your own content. More than the responsibility of making it available, hosting it means that you own it. This is preferable for many reasons. You can personally ensure that your content is never lost or used in an unethical way.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":149,"length":10,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"66dr","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bs82v","text":"Designing a minimal engine","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ccsgb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a72vm","text":"I began by outlining the smallest feature set that would be immediately useful. I came up with the following list:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"67rqi","text":"Ability to create blog posts","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9v7cg","text":"Ability to render blog posts on a web page","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7k8d0","text":"Ability to customize the blog title","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"63lcb","text":" The purpose of a blog engine is, unsurprisingly, to deliver blogs to readers! What's that, you ask? No custom flashing red text on a dark green background for your Christmas tree farm's blog? I did say minimal, didn't I?","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"402gc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4goem","text":"The next thing to consider is the system's operational environment. In this case I settled early on a simple LAMP stack onboard a raspberry pi. I made this hardware decision early due to my excitement about keeping a permanent pi server at home. The software stack is easy to setup and learn, and I was happy to dive a little deeper into it. My capstone project at UAFS made use of a LAMP stack and it turned out quite well!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":100,"length":19,"key":0},{"offset":130,"length":12,"key":1},{"offset":345,"length":24,"key":2}],"data":{}},{"key":"1s5ur","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a4250","text":"For the software design I wanted to contiue with the trend of simplicity.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fdule","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3nn36","text":"Blog posts","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6c8e7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7cbfl","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fot2c","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4n56e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4iook","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1p6f9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4k6an","text":" I hope anyone looking for a simple solution to hosting their blog locally can take something useful away from this one. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"coc4r","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8alak","text":"","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2aj9e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"79rq0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}]}